|  13 |   100 |
|  14 |    99 |
|  15 |    98 |
We need 14 periods, so RSI is calculated on Day 15.

- Step 1: Price changes (Δ):
Δ = Close today​ − Close yesterday​
| Day | Close |  Δ |
| --: | ----: | -: |
|   2 |   102 | +2 |
|   3 |   101 | -1 |
|   4 |   103 | +2 |
|   5 |   104 | +1 |
|   6 |   103 | -1 |
|   7 |   105 | +2 |
|   8 |   106 | +1 |
|   9 |   104 | -2 |
|  10 |   103 | -1 |
|  11 |   102 | -1 |
|  12 |   101 | -1 |
|  13 |   100 | -1 |
|  14 |    99 | -1 |
|  15 |    98 | -1 |

- Step 2: Separate Gains and Losses:

Gains = positive Δ, else 0
Losses = absolute value of negative Δ, else 0
| Day |  Δ | Gain | Loss |
| --: | -: | ---: | ---: |
|   2 | +2 |    2 |    0 |
|   3 | -1 |    0 |    1 |
|   4 | +2 |    2 |    0 |
|   5 | +1 |    1 |    0 |
|   6 | -1 |    0 |    1 |
|   7 | +2 |    2 |    0 |
|   8 | +1 |    1 |    0 |
|   9 | -2 |    0 |    2 |
|  10 | -1 |    0 |    1 |
|  11 | -1 |    0 |    1 |
|  12 | -1 |    0 |    1 |
|  13 | -1 |    0 |    1 |
|  14 | -1 |    0 |    1 |
|  15 | -1 |    0 |    1 |

- Step 3: Average Gain & Average Loss (14 periods):
Average Gain = (2+2+1+2+1​) / 14 = 0.571
Average Loss = (1+1+2+1+1+1+1+1+1) / 14 = 0.714

- Step 4: Relative Strength (RS):
RS = Avg Gain / Avg Loss
RS = 0.571 / 0.714 = 0.80

- Step 5: RSI formula (final step):
RSI = 100 - 100 / (1 + RS)

RSI = 100 - 100 / (1.80) = (100 - 55.56) = 44.44

- Final RSI result:
| Metric       | Value     |
| ------------ | --------- |
| Average Gain | 0.571     |
| Average Loss | 0.714     |
| RS           | 0.80      |
| **RSI**      | **44.44** |

- How to interpret RSI = 44.44:

| RSI   | Meaning    | Action |
| ----- | ---------- | ------ |
| < 30  | Oversold   | BUY    |
| 30–70 | Neutral    | HOLD   |
| > 70  | Overbought | SELL   |

44.44 → HOLD